{"title_page": "Luxgen S5", "text_new": "{{Infobox automobile\n|image=LUXGEN S5 TURBO ECO HYPER 2016.01 001.jpg\n|name=Luxgen S5 \n|aka=Luxgen S5 turbo Eco Hyper\n|manufacturer=[[Luxgen]]\n|production=2012&ndash;present\n|assembly= [[Miaoli City|Miaoli]], [[Taiwan]]\n|engine= 1.8 L, 2.0 L [[Turbocharged]] [[Inline-four engine|I-4]]\n|transmission=[[Aisin]] 6-speed [[Manumatic]] transmission\n| wheelbase = {{Convert|2720|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|length= {{convert|4690|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|width= {{convert|1805|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|height= {{convert|1490|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|body_style=[[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n|weight= {{convert|1390|-|1410|kg|abbr=on}}\n|layout=[[FF layout|Front Engine, Front Wheel Drive]]\n|predecessor = \n|class = [[Compact car]] \n|related= [[Luxgen U6]]\n}}\nThe '''Luxgen S5''', or previously known as the '''Luxgen5''' Sedan, is a 5-seater compact sedan [[car]] produced by the [[Taiwan]]ese car company [[Luxgen]].\n\n\n\n==Overview==\nThe model is the first car developed entirely in Taiwan. It was styled by the [[Hua-chuang Automobile Information Technical Center|HAITEC]] Design Center led by [[James C. Shyr|James Shyr]]. It was unveiled in November 2011, known as the electric concept car [[Neora]] at the [[Taipei Auto Show]] and then officially launched in the second quarter of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luxgen Neora concept unveiled|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/111042632929/luxgen-neora-concept-unveiled|publisher=Worldcarfans|date=2011-08-26}}</ref> Luxgen5 Sedan is the first sedan of Luxgen series. It has a 1.8-liter [[turbo charged]] petrol engine or a 2.0-liter 4-cylinder [[turbo charged]] petrol engine giving 191&nbsp;hp&nbsp;hp/28&nbsp;kgm (2.0&nbsp;L) and 171&nbsp;hp&nbsp;hp/27.1&nbsp;kgm (1.8&nbsp;L), thanks to the new [[Eco Hyper]] technology. It also has Think+ and Eagle View features for night-vision and 360 degrees vision. Beside, the new [[Think+]] system can attach to most cellphones like [[HTC]], [[Meizu]], [[ZTE]], and even [[Huawei]] . The starting price is around $23,000.<ref>{{cite web|title= LUXGEN5 Sedan |url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/10/b1090735.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/10/b1090735+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|publisher=AutoNet.com.tw|date=2011-03-10}}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"150px\">\nFile:LUXGEN S5 TURBO ECO HYPER 2016.01 002.jpg|Luxgen S5 (Facelift)\nFile:Luxgen 5 Sedan China 2015-04-13.jpg|Luxgen S5 (Pre-facelift)\nFile:LUXGEN_S5_TURBO_2014_02.JPG|Luxgen S5 (Pre-facelift)\n</gallery>\n{{clear}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.motoplex.com.do/ Luxgen Dominican Republic]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160512154605/http://www.luxgen-motor.com.tw/TC/Car/s5 Luxgen S5 Official Taiwanese Website]\n\n{{Luxgen}}\n\n[[Category:Luxgen vehicles|S5]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2011]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Front-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Compact cars]]\n[[Category:Sedans]]\n\n\n{{car-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox automobile\n|image=LUXGEN S5 TURBO ECO HYPER 2016.01 001.jpg\n|name=Luxgen S5 \n|aka=Luxgen S5 turbo Eco Hyper\n|manufacturer=[[Luxgen]]\n|production=2012&ndash;present\n|assembly= [[Miaoli City|Miaoli]], [[Taiwan]]\n|engine= 1.8 L, 2.0 L [[Turbocharged]] [[Inline-four engine|I-4]]\n|transmission=[[Aisin]] 6-speed [[Manumatic]] transmission\n| wheelbase = {{Convert|2720|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|length= {{convert|4690|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|width= {{convert|1805|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|height= {{convert|1490|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n|body_style=[[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n|weight= {{convert|1390|-|1410|kg|abbr=on}}\n|layout=[[FF layout|Front Engine, Front Wheel Drive]]\n|predecessor = \n|class = [[Compact car]] \n|related= [[Luxgen U6]]\n}}\nThe '''Luxgen S5''', or previously known as the '''Luxgen5''' Sedan, is a 5-seater compact sedan [[car]] produced by the [[Taiwan]]ese car company [[Luxgen]].\n\n\n\n==Overview==\nThe model is the first car developed entirely in Taiwan. It was styled by the [[Hua-chuang Automobile Information Technical Center|HAITEC]] Design Center led by [[James C. Shyr|James Shyr]]. It was unveiled in November 2011, known as the electric concept car [[Neora]] at the [[Taipei Auto Show]] and then officially launched in the second quarter of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Luxgen Neora concept unveiled|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/111042632929/luxgen-neora-concept-unveiled|publisher=Worldcarfans|date=2011-08-26}}</ref> Luxgen5 Sedan is the first sedan of Luxgen series. It has a 1.8-liter [[turbo charged]] petrol engine or a 2.0-liter 4-cylinder [[turbo charged]] petrol engine giving 191&nbsp;hp&nbsp;hp/28&nbsp;kgm (2.0&nbsp;L) and 171&nbsp;hp&nbsp;hp/27.1&nbsp;kgm (1.8&nbsp;L), thanks to the new [[Eco Hyper]] technology. It also has Think+ and Eagle View features for night-vision and 360 degrees vision. Beside, the new [[Think+]] system can attach to most cellphones like [[HTC]], [[Meizu]], [[ZTE]], and even [[Huawei]] . The starting price is around $23,000.<ref>{{cite web|title= LUXGEN5 Sedan |url=http://www.autonet.com.tw/cgi-bin/view.cgi?/news/2011/10/b1090735.ti+a2+a3+a4+a5+b1+/news/2011/10/b1090735+b3+d6+c1+c2+c3+e1+e2+e3+e5+f1|publisher=AutoNet.com.tw|date=2011-03-10}}</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"150px\">\nFile:LUXGEN S5 TURBO ECO HYPER 2016.01 002.jpg|Luxgen S5 (Facelift)\nFile:Luxgen 5 Sedan China 2015-04-13.jpg|Luxgen S5 (Pre-facelift)\nFile:LUXGEN_S5_TURBO_2014_02.JPG|Luxgen S5 (Pre-facelift)\n</gallery>\n{{clear}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.motoplex.com.do/ Luxgen Dominican Republic]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160512154605/http://www.luxgen-motor.com.tw/TC/Car/s5 Luxgen S5 Official Taiwanese Website]\n\n{{Luxgen}}\n\n[[Category:Luxgen vehicles|S5]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2011]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Front-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Compact cars]]\n[[